    "description": "Made from wood, animal horn and sinew laminated together,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">the drawn bow stores more energy than wood for the same length of bow, allowing a&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">powerful bow in a shorter length. The bow is able to be used from horseback.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">Manufacture requires a range of components to source, takes longer than a wood bow&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">and the finished bow is more sensitive to moisture. Leather cases are often made to&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: var(--s2d6-light-color); font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit;\">carry the bows in. Also known as: Mongol bow, recurve bow, Turkish bow, Manchu bow.</span>",
